<concept id="topic_1_5" >
  <title  id="title__Toc272567194">Conventions</title>
	<shortdesc>The N1QL syntax described in the documentation uses some notational conventions that you
    need to be familiar with.</shortdesc>
  <conbody >
    <table><title>Notational conventions for N1QL syntax</title>
      <tgroup cols="4">
        <colspec colname="1" colwidth="2102*"/>
        <colspec colname="2" colwidth="1081*"/>
        <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1831*"/>
        <colspec colname="4" colwidth="3816*"/>
        <thead><row><entry>
          <p>Convention</p>
        </entry>
          <entry><p>Notation</p></entry>
          <entry><p>Example</p></entry>
          <entry><p>Description</p></entry>
        </row>
        </thead><tbody><row>
          <entry><p>Upper case</p></entry>
          <entry><p>Â </p></entry>
          <entry><p>SELECT</p></entry>
          <entry><p>Indicates keywords.</p></entry></row>
          <row><entry><p>Single or double quotes</p></entry>
            <entry><p>' or "</p></entry>
            <entry><p>city = 'London'</p></entry>
            <entry><p>Surrounds expressions that are specific query items. Either single or double quotes can be used.</p></entry>
          </row>
          <row><entry><p>Square brackets</p></entry>
            <entry><p>[ ]</p></entry>
            <entry><p>[NOT] BETWEEN</p></entry>
            <entry><p>Indicates optional parts.</p></entry>
          </row>
          <row><entry><p>Pipe </p></entry>
            <entry><p>|</p></entry>
            <entry><p>AND | OR</p></entry>
            <entry><p >Separates alternatives.</p></entry>
          </row>
          <row><entry><p>Parentheses</p></entry>
            <entry><p>( )</p>
            </entry>
            <entry><p>COUNT(*)</p></entry>
            <entry><p>Functions to perform an operation.</p></entry>
          </row>
          <row><entry><p>Bold square, curly brackets and parentheses</p></entry>
            <entry><p><b>[]</b>, <b>{}</b>, <b>()</b> </p>
            </entry>
            <entry><p><codeph><b>[</b>element<b>]</b></codeph></p></entry>
            <entry><p>Indicate that the brackets or parentheses are required in the syntax when a N1QL statement is
								constructed. </p></entry>
          </row>
          
 
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
  </conbody>
</concept>
